A DRIVER has died in a crash between two lorries on a motorway.
The accident involving an articulated lorry and one carrying cattle happened on the M74 near Elvanfoot, South Lanarkshire , at about 1.20pm yesterday.
The 49-year-old driver of the cattle float died at the scene, police said.
The 45-year-old driver of the other lorry was not injured. Police are appealing for any witnesses to contact them.
Constable Kenneth Beeby said: &quot;I would appeal to anyone who has information to contact police via the non-emergency number 101.&quot;
